Basil HILL v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6347. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. July 14, 1960. Wendell Stockton, Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. Paul W. Cress, U. S. Atty., and Erwin A. Cook, Asst. U. S. Atty., Oklahoma City, Old., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
